Being the commencement of <span id="page_224">p. 224</span> the affair,
the arrow was considered "specially important and was shot off
reverently with prayers to the Gods,—" whence its name."

<span id="fn_1366"></span>[221:19](kj073.htm#fr_1370.md) *I.e.*,
"excrements \[fœdatæ\] bracæ." But it is not at all probable that this
